sec.p:
In addition, to select the studies to be reviewed, the following inclusion criteria were used:
The studies were performed on humans, either children or adults;
A comparison was performed between either: (i) ASD patients and healthy controls or (ii) ASD patient with different subtypes;
The studies’ outcome consisted of specific EEG features of ASD, not its comorbidities;
The studies included patients diagnosed according to the clinical criteria from DSM III onward;
The studies were published between 1980 and May 2016;
The studies were performed using EEG and the signal was analyzed using spectral analysis, functional connectivity measures, or information dynamics methods.
